                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/92.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-03T20:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Since sending my June 3, 2 p.m., re new decree collection customs Charges, I have
                    conferred with Sr. F. Villareal, Secretary Communications of Constitutionalists
                    and he informs me that decree applies only to export Charges, bar Charges, and
                    oil production taxes, and will not be applied to import duties. Rule is based on
                    theory that all exports are sold abroad on gold basis.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
